    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A beam of brilliant light flashes out from your hand in a 5-foot-wide, 60-foot-long line. Each creature in the line must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes [[/damage 6d8 type=radiant]] damage and is &amp;Reference[condition=blinded] until your next turn. On a successful save, it takes half as much damage and isn't &amp;Reference[condition=blinded] by this spell. Undead and oozes have disadvantage on this saving throw.</p><p>You can create a new line of radiance as your action on any turn until the spell ends.</p><p>For the duration, a mote of brilliant radiance shines in your hand. It sheds bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. This light is sunlight.</p></div>",
